2.body: Java is a compiled language, meaning that the source code needs to be transformed into bytecode by the java compiler! After compilation, the program can be run by the java virtual machine! Java files look like this: test.java : sourcecode written in java-syntax! humanly readible! test.class : bytecode (machine code), which can only be read and executed by the java virtual machine! .java files are usually stored in src (source), while .class files are stored in bin (binary) directory.
